# Stable salt used by packages/affiliate-helper/js/affiliate-helper.js
# to hash plaintext campaign strings (e.g. "web-portfolio-discipline-hero")
# into opaque tokens (e.g. "web-a1b2c3d4e5") at build time.
#
# Generate once: openssl rand -hex 32
#
# This same value MUST be set in three places so the mint side can decode:
#   1. This file (.env) on your local machine (gitignored)
#   2. GitHub Actions repo secret named CAMPAIGN_HASH_SALT
#      (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret)
#   3. ~/.poolpat/.env on the machine that runs poolpat-mint
#
# Treat this like the Partnerize keys — rotate only if compromised; rotating
# breaks decoding of any clicks recorded before the rotation.
CAMPAIGN_HASH_SALT=
